                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201028-40-off237 t18201028-40-crimeloc240"></join>. On the 21st of September, at eight o'clock at night, I missed a pair of boots, which hung on the wainscoat, in a quarter of an hour I missed another pair. I went down Lambeth-hill, which is one door from my shop; I saw the prisoner with another man, and saw the boots in his hand - he instantly dropped them, and I caught them as they fell. I secured him, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked them up.</p>
